This is true for all tasks. I have to have failsafes for EVERYTHING.
Don't have the spoons to cook? Eat sandwich, or heat soup, as it doesn't need that much supervision.
Is it easy? Absolutely not. As i have to know how to get myself that far, and knowing that i Will fail and know that the next day i might fail as well.

Just today i started creating a cleaning schedule with my councelor... As i am bad at it. What does it look like? One Task, one small room per day, plus plenty of time. So that even on a bad day i can do it, without overstepping my mental health. Small Steps.
Routine is not just getting up. Routine is about cleaning, cooking. Anything. I have to put failsafes on anything if i want it to happen.
Adhd'ers like myself have trouble getting to sleep on regular hours. I can try, but it will not happen. Same for chronically ill People.
